    "en": {
      "title": "LTTE member and former ASP acquitted in Jeyaraj murder case",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Gampaha High Court Judge Mr. Sahan Mapa Bandara today (01) ordered the acquittal of two suspects who had been arrested for the murder of former Minister Jeyaraj Fernandopulle and 16 others and were in custody.",
        "Former LTTE member Selvaraja Kirubakaran and former Assistant Superintendent of Police Senarath Laxman Kure have been acquitted.",
        "Former LTTE member Selvaraja Kirubakaran Gampaha was charged by the Attorney General with 31 charges of killing 16 people including former Minister Jeyaraj Fernandopulle and attempting to kill 84 other people and conspiring to kill 16 people in Weliveriya on April 6, 2008. Charges were filed against Superintendent of Police Senarath Laxman Kure."
      ],
